reviewText: This was a real disappointment. Most of the film is dry tedious shots of "experts" talking about Death Valley versus footage of the actual place.

I had hoped for a serious, albeit brief, expose' about geology in Death Valley.
This disc is awful.  Anecdotes from PhD's ... boring anecdotes .

If you're looking for pretty, scenic videos, these aren't for you. If you want in-depth information about our National Parks, you'll love this entire series. They tell you not only about the park, but about the ecology and history of the entire area.
